Cell["\<\
The  higher  \[Mu]  fitted  to  all  colonies  obviously  does  not  \
reproduce  the experimental regrowth probability. 
We  therefore go back  to  the  smaller  \[Mu] = 1.6 x 10^-10,  which  fits  \
better P(regrowth) and also P(N_mutants) (\[Mu] was fitted to it).
The new model includes filamentation but this does not affect the \
distribution P(N_mutants), so no need to optimize \[Mu] again.\
\>", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9582074248206606`*^9, 3.958207473762855*^9}, {
  3.9582075258914356`*^9, 3.958207553789085*^9}, {3.9582076562212505`*^9, 
  3.9582077229180965`*^9}, {3.9610341860876102`*^9, 
  3.961034299919054*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"787d13b9-28f8-324b-9f0a-\
053bd1fe6fe1"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Single allele model for STR with filamentation, fitted to the P(N_mut) data \
(only large colonies)\
\>", "Section",
